	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wizards are in my opinon one of the best classes in the game. I am currently lvl 52 and sure it took me a lot of time and effort to get there but I can do a lot of things in the game while other classes are forced to group from lvl 30 or 40 and ahead. I can solo I can port I can kite (and quad kite of course, once you quad kite you won´t be able to stop doing it it is just great to be able to kill 4 blue mobs while other classes can not kill a high green solo).<br> Until lvl 30 life can be a bit hard for a wizard because of all the melee twinks out thee with 3 or 4k weapons and they can outdamage us very easly at early levels. Our DDs are very good not only for their damage, wich at early levels can be the same as druid´s DDs, but their dmg mana ratio they consume much less mana than druid or any other class spells, and our resists (if you have played any caster in a raid besides a wizard you know what I mean) <br> At lvl 20 I´d suggest Lake of III Omen just go there and nowhere else until 30. It is tru that the zone is overcrowded but it is a very nice zone you can solo n the shoreline near sarnak fort whle looking for a group in the fort or the mill.<br> At 30 I went to Splitpaw until 33, dangerous zone but you have to get used to work in dungeons at least a bit and the zone is very good (with a good and balanced group with chanter and cleric of course)<br> At 33 and until 40-43 go to the Overthere and do the same you did in LOIO(lake of III Omen) solo while looking for a group and try to lear to quad kite here, basically what you do is agro 4 mobs with&nbsp;&nbsp;flux staff or a fast DD like a lvl 4 one and run in circles until they are close to eachother then Bonds of force then circle of force until they are dead. You must have 190+ int for that or you will run out of mana and you will have to zone. Wait and see how much exp you can get there.<br> And about jboots forget about them until lvl 50, buy 2 or 3 sow potions and in LOIO and in OT (overthere) ask for sow to any nearby druid or ranger or shaman, they´d be glad to help you since the spell cost them just a few mana, especially if you can affor a small donation.ç<br> At 43 more or less go Dreadlands and do the same solo while looking for a group and you will get to 50 in no time. Those zones are crowded but that is not bad because you can get free sow and free clarity and also solo while looking for a group so you will develop good soloing skills and good group skills.<br> And once you get to 50 you will need no advise on whre to hunt and you will be an awesome Damage dealer capable of casting a DD that can hit for 1120 dmg and at 51 you get a spell wich "only" hits for 654 or something like that but costs 215 mana and casts in less than 3 seconds (since you´ll have youe evocation maxed by then) so at 51 with 200+ int and a few mana items you´ll be able to dish about 7300 dmg if you don´t get resisted nwo how many classes can do that without being in a group? not many and the ones that can do it can do it with the help of a pet ot with Dot spells (damage over time) and that is no the same as being able to do that in just 33 seconds is it ). Oh and you can also port and trasocate, and chain stun, and aoe, and snare, and root and...<br> So yes wizards are a very very very bad class :P<br><br>PD: sorry about the spelling or gramar errors but I am too tired to check it and I am from Spain so english is not my mothertongue so.... :)<br><br>Koradris Hopebringer lvl 52 Chaneller<br>"Wild Knigths" The Rathe server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
