	   <a name=99522282868158></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99522282868158><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99522282868158>RE: Tactics for Soloing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99522282868158#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=66819><span id= >eljefe</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 15th 2:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm level 9, my Alteration is maxed at 50, and Fade just isn't doing it for me.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm hunting in Lesser Faydark, which is hilly, but even when I'm standing on the lip of a valley I just don't go very far.  I've had Fade ever since level 4, and it's never helped me that much.  /shrug<br><br>I bought Fade at level 4 to max my Alteration, but Alteration never got maxed until I bought Root.  I got Root at level 6 when I was starting to group and saw the need for poor man's crowd contol, but I found it to be an invaluable aid for soloing.  Casting Fade whenever it seemed appropriate, my Alteration only got up to about 14 by level 6.  I was in the upper 20's by level 7, and maxed it at 40 before I hit level 8.  It's been maxed soon after I ding ever since, just from hunting.<br><br>My tactic is to Root at max range (200', the same as my shock spells), then chain-cast my best nuke until the mob is dead, the mob breaks root, or I'm OoM.<br><br>If the mob breaks root, I immediately recast root.  I then back up a few steps, turn slightly to the left or right (prevents interrupts), then nuke.  As soon as I see the damage message on the mob, I back up, turn, and cast again.  I do this until the mob is at max range again.<br><br>When rooting and nuking, staying at range is important.  The mob WILL break root when you least want it to, and your little wizard butt will get munched if you don't land another root sooner or later.  It is much easier to land a root on a mob that is rushing toward you but still out of melee range than it is to land one on a mob that is hitting (and interrupting) you.  You can't cast during your nuke's recast time, so you might as well be backing up to maintain that cushion of safety between you and the mob.<br><br>Root and Nuke can be used to solo camps, as well.  Get at max range, and root the highest mob in the camp.  Everything else blue and up will aggro you, but you can get another root off on one before they get to you.  You now have two root-parked mobs, and one or more on you.  Auto-attack and root the third, back up, and cast away.  Be ready to switch targets and recast root quickly, since the parked mobs rarely stay that way until you've finished with their cousins.  Tricky and challenging, but very impressive and good experience if you live.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
