	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, you can get TBoots much cheaper - <br>1) go to sol B. If you're high enough, get in a Kobold group. Killing the kobolds raises your faction with the Solusek Mining Co, the faction of the gnome that sells the TBoots.<br> If you're NOT high enough, find a strong kobold group that will let you hit the kobold once while they are killing it - that way you'll get the faction. Your goal is to make it to indifferent, so the time spent doing this will depend on your starting faction.<br><br>2) get a charisma buff, or some charisma gear. Make sure that your CHA is at least 105.<br><br>If you are indifferent to the gnomes, and your cha is 105 or greater, the boots will cost you<br>5250 pp.<br><br>Also, the TBoots are marginally slower than a sow from a caster of the same level. I suspect that the JBoots are as well.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
